'''Guru-da-Gaddi''' is an important [[Sikh]] religious event held every 3 November. The event honors when the tenth and last [[Sikh Guru]]s when they said 'the next Guru would be the Holy Sikh Book' [[Guru Granth Sahib]].  [[Guru Gobind Singh]], declared that [[Guru Granth Sahib]] would from that moment on be the Guru or the Guiding Force. The message was delivered on 3 November 1708 by [[Guru Gobind Singh]] at [[Nanded]] in the [[States of India|state]] of [[Maharashtra]] in [[India]]. [[Guru Gobind Singh]] Ji established [[Khalsa]] and conferred the status of the Guru to the [[Guru Granth Sahib]] and elevated it as the everlasting Guru.

This event is commemorated with a festival/ritual that starts with [[Diwali]] in [[India]] - a Hindu Sikh festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.webindia123.com/news/articles/India/20080926/1063510.html |title=Preparations for tricentenary of Guru-Da-Gaddi in full swing |publisher=News.webindia123.com |date= |accessdate=2013-06-22}}</ref> The tercentenary celebrations of the occasion are being referred at Guru-da-gaddi and are being celebrated on 3 November 2008 in Nanded in [[Maharshtra]].<ref>[http://www.maharashtra.gov.in/english/chiefminister/On_path_of_progress.pdf ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070316122505/http://www.maharashtra.gov.in/english/chiefminister/On_path_of_progress.pdf |date=16 March 2007 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.chennaivision.com/enews/2008/Oct/02/Nanded-admin-citizens-all-set-for-Guru-Da-Gaddi-celebrations.asp ]{{dead link|date=June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indopia.in/India-usa-uk-news/print-385757.html |title=indiareport.com |publisher=Indopia.in |date= |accessdate=2013-06-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ddinews.gov.in/Current%20Affairs |title=www.ddinews.com |publisher=www.ddinews.com |date= |accessdate=2013-06-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.outlookindia.com/pti_news.asp?id=616948 |title=Mah Congress gets into election mode with Sonia visit &#124; news.outlookindia.com |publisher=Outlookindia.com |date=2008-10-06 |accessdate=2013-06-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sikhnet.com/news/honor-300th-anniversary-guru-gaddi |title=Honor the 300th Anniversary of Guru Gaddi |publisher=SikhNet |date=2008-10-17 |accessdate=2013-06-22}}</ref> The occasion comes after celebrations of [[300 Years of Khalsa]] panth established by [[Guru Gobind Singh]] ji in 1699.

