{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}}
'''Lenin was a mushroom''' ({{lang-ru|Ленин — гриб}}) was a highly influential televised [[hoax]] by [[Soviet]] musician [[Sergey Kuryokhin]] and reporter [[Sergey Leonidovich Sholokhov|Sergey Sholokhov]]. It was first broadcast on 17 May 1991 on [[Petersburg – Channel 5|Leningrad Television]].<ref>{{Cite journal|first=Alexei |last=Yurchak |authorlink=Alexei Yurchak |date=Summer 2011 |title=A Parasite from Outer Space: How Sergei Kurekhin Proved That Lenin Was a Mushroom |journal=Slavic Review |volume=70 |issue=2 |pages=307 |doi=10.5612/slavicreview.70.2.0307 |issn=0037-6779 |jstor=10.5612/slavicreview.70.2.0307}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://forum-msk.org/material/politic/5261278.html|title=Десакрализация образа власти|website=МСК|accessdate=2018-06-20}}</ref>

The hoax took the form of an interview on the television program ''Pyatoe Koleso'' (The Fifth Wheel). In the interview, Kuryokhin, impersonating a historian, narrated his findings that [[Vladimir Lenin]] consumed large quantities of [[psychedelic mushrooms]] and eventually became a mushroom himself. Kuryokhin arrived at his conclusion through a long series of logical fallacies and appeals to the authority of various "sources" (such as [[Carlos Castaneda]], the [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]], and [[Konstantin Tsiolkovsky]]), creating the illusion of a reasoned and plausible logical chain.

The timing of the hoax played a large role in its success, coming as it did during the [[Glasnost]] period when the ebbing of [[censorship]] in the [[Soviet Union]] led to many revelations about the country's history, often presented in sensational form.<ref name=Atlas>{{cite web |first=Eric |last=Grundhauser |url=https://www.atlasobscura.com/articles/lenin-mushroom-hoax-russia? |title=How Vladimir Lenin Became a Mushroom |website=[[Atlas Obscura]] |date=5 December 2017 }}</ref> Furthermore, Soviet television had, up to that point, been regarded by its audience as conservative in style and content. As a result, a large number of Soviet citizens (one estimate<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://new.topos.ru/article/2139|title=Диалоги с Сергеем Жариковым на исходе лета|author=Иоффе Д.|date=2004-03-12|publisher=Topos|accessdate=2018-09-19}}</ref> puts the number at 11,250,000 audience members) took the deadpan "interview" at face value, in spite of the absurd claims presented.

Sholokhov has said that perhaps the most notable result of the show was an appeal by a group of party members to the Leningrad Regional Committee of the [[CPSU]] to clarify the veracity of Kuryokhin's claim. According to Sholokhov, in response to the request one of the top regional functionaries stated that "Lenin could not have been a mushroom" because "a mammal cannot be a plant."<ref name=Atlas/><ref>{{cite web|last=Mishenin|first=Dmitry |title=Тихий Шолохов |trans-title=Quiet flows the Sholokhov |type=Interview of S. Sholokhov with ''Krestyanka'' magazine|url=http://www.krestyanka.ru/archive/year2008/dec/dec_349.html|date=December 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081214123744/http://krestyanka.ru/archive/year2008/dec/dec_349.html|archive-date=14 December 2008 |language=ru}}</ref> Modern [[Taxonomy (biology)|taxonomy]] classifies mushrooms as [[Fungus|fungi]], a separate [[Kingdom (biology)|kingdom]] from [[plant]]s.

The incident has served as a watershed moment in Soviet (and Russian) culture and has often been used as proof of the gullibility of the masses.{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}

